rk.house.gov/member_info/electionInfo/2012election.pdf |title= Statists of the Presidential and Congressional Election of November 6, 2012 |first= Karen L. |last= Haas |authorlink= Karen L. Haas |date= February 28, 2013 |publisher =[[Clerk of the United States House of Representatives]] |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141104054942/http://clerk.house.gov/member_info/electionInfo/2012election.pdf |archive-date= 2014-11-04 |deadurl= no }}</ref>}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|\n | party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n | candidate  = [[Jim Matheson]] (incumbent)\n | votes      = 119,803\n | percentage = 48.84\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n | party      = Republican Party (United States)\n | candidate  = Mia B. Love\n | votes      = 119,035\n | percentage = 48.53\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n | party      = Libertarian Party (United States)\n | candidate  = Jim L. Vein\n | votes      = 6,439\n | percentage = 2.63\n}}\n{{Election box total no change|\n | votes      = 245,277\n | percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link without swing|\n | winner     = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Politics of Utah]]\n*[[List of United States Representatives from Utah]]\n*[[Women in the United States House of Representatives]]\n*[[United States House of Representatives]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite news |url= http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2012/05/01/house-candidate-and-rising-gop-star-is-black-female-and-mormon |title= House candidate and rising GOP star is black, female \u2013 and Mormon |first= Dan |last= Gilgoff |date= May 1, 2012 |publisher= CNN |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20141104234948/http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2012/05/01/house-candidate-and-rising-gop-star-is-black-female-and-mormon |archive-date= 2014-11-04 |dead-url= no }}\n\n==External links==\n{{co